{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-awesome-timeline-js","path":"/kyleterry/awesome-radio/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Track Awesome List"}},"awesomeList":{"repo":"kyleterry/awesome-radio","descriptionHTML":"<div>Awesome radio stuff</div>","description":"Awesome radio stuff"},"awesomeListMeta":{"readmeParsedAt":"2021-06-27T23:33:38.796Z"},"allAwesomeItem":{"nodes":[{"categoryHTML":"<h2>General</h2><h3>Links</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.hamqsl.com/solar2.html\">N0NBH's Solar-Terrestrial Data</a> - Current</li>","updatedAt":"2018-06-01T20:10:12.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>CB</h2><h3>Links</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.rightchannelradios.com/\">Right Channel Radios</a> - Good online shop</li>","updatedAt":"2014-12-19T06:30:28.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>SDR (Software Defined Radio)</h2><h3>Hardware</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><strong>Recommended starter hardware</strong> On the low end,\n<a href=\"http://sdr.osmocom.org/trac/wiki/rtl-sdr\">RTL-SDR</a> is a super-cheap usb\ndongle, around which a thriving community has been founded.</li>","updatedAt":"2014-12-19T06:30:28.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>SDR (Software Defined Radio)</h2><h3>Hardware</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>On the other side of the cost spectrum, <a href=\"http://www.pervices.com/\">pervices</a>\nmakes some really high-throughput, PCIe devices for when you need to log all\nthe traffic ever. The software and community support for this is less good,\nthough (for which you can blame @outofculture).</li>","updatedAt":"2014-12-19T06:30:28.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>SDR (Software Defined Radio)</h2><h3>Hardware</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>You can also browse through the <a href=\"https://gnuradio.org/redmine/projects/gnuradio/wiki/Hardware\">big\nlist</a> of all\ncompatible hardware.</li>","updatedAt":"2014-12-19T06:30:28.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>SDR (Software Defined Radio)</h2><h3>Hardware</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>Antennas are their own body of options and tradeof